An NFI typically consists of:

-The AI model itself

-Metadata describing the model's capabilities and performance metrics

-An NFT on a blockchain representing ownership and containing a link to the AI asset

-Smart contracts governing the usage rights and all revenue sharing

just like with NFTs, "non-fungible" means that each AI model is unique and not replaceable 

with  cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin, each unit is identical and replacable (fungible). 

NFIs capture the unique characteristics and capabilities of specific AI models.
